ef":"621baea2-2874-4fea-9514-40d85bca05d0"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"e71ea52e-7e7f-4201-b5f9-d3a4e9a37c14"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"0.05","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"0bba15cf-0ce2-4552-be04-79521579c5bd"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"479d3061-90f0-409b-9f10-acf997975028"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"1.60","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"c0d9b2bf-bf28-4a36-aa5d-7d0b008d0a55"}],"object":"block","type":"table-row","ref":"fcd02991-129e-47c6-abac-e644ad6157e3"}],"object":"block","type":"table-body","ref":"0f6763bd-6f50-4a56-bb65-5bf40774a58f"}],"object":"block","type":"table","ref":"f76b33ff-5a0f-406b-8938-49a0fcab7a0c"}]}},"ref":"0f435038-cd9d-4eba-aecd-309a6698c245"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"775fa9ab-fcd9-4ff0-8033-a9bd097596b8","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"We plot the data from ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"cf88cbcb-a0bd-45ae-b2c9-25799f7aeac3","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Table 23.1","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"b159b4d0-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":" in ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"679e70da-3807-4175-9ed4-a12c809bebb6","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Figure 23.8","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"b167be90-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":", where we compare hedging with options to the alternative of hedging with a forward contract or not hedging at all. If the firm does not hedge at all, its cost for euros is simply the spot exchange rate. If the firm hedges with a forward contract, it locks in the cost of euros at the forward exchange rate and the firm’s cost is fixed. As ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"0dde46e1-bb80-42a8-9956-40c06154bf88","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Figure 23.8","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"b167be90-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":" shows, hedging with options represents a middle ground: The firm puts a ","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"cap","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]},{"object":"text","text":" on its potential cost but will benefit if the euro depreciates in value.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"0abc17e7-1723-4f37-84c9-25c38e61eaab"},{"type":"stage-element-image","config":{"url":{"$ambrosia":"aero:asset:upload","urn":"urn:aero:dc9f3da0-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","asset":{"urn":"urn:aero:dc9f3da0-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","asset":{"assetProvider":"ALFRESCO","id":"dc9f3da0-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","assetMediaType":"image","assetVisibility":"GLOBAL","ownerId":"e88133a0-8dc4-11eb-964e-4d7e264c9958","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","alfrescoId":"c9988b5d-4dac-4b27-8c7d-1845641e674c","name":"FG_23_008.jpg","version":"2.0","lastModifiedDate":1664998400,"lastSyncDate":1665085941},"source":{"small":{"width":431,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dc9f3da0-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c/small/d8e45808a0e189434e63468703076a82.jpeg","height":300},"original":{"width":862,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dc9f3da0-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c/medium/d8e45808a0e189434e63468703076a82.jpeg","height":600},"medium":{"width":862,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dc9f3da0-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c/medium/d8e45808a0e189434e63468703076a82.jpeg","height":600},"thumb":{"width":215,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dc9f3da0-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c/thumb/d8e45808a0e189434e63468703076a82.jpeg","height":150}},"metadata":{"altText":"","workURN":"","caption":"<p>The forward hedge locks in an exchange rate and so eliminates all risk. Not hedging leaves the firm fully exposed. Hedging with an option allows the firm to benefit if the exchange rate falls and protects the firm from a very large increase.</p>","alfrescoPath":"bronte-e2e-testing-qaint/documentLibrary/BV E2E Test/[10-05-2022] Berk","originalAssetName":"FG_23_008.jpg","longDesc":"","height":"557"}}},"alt":"","caption":"<p>The forward hedge locks in an exchange rate and so eliminates all risk. Not hedging leaves the firm fully exposed. Hedging with an option allows the firm to benefit if the exchange rate falls and protects the firm from a very large increase.</p>","layout":{"captionPosition":"Below"},"credit":"","activityLabel":"Figure 23.8","activityTitle":"Comparison of Hedging the Exchange Rate Using a Forward Contract, an Option, or No Hedge"},"height":557,"ref":"dde12372-5690-48bc-8ff2-435dd5fe2d39"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-three","ref":"2905879c-2b9f-4e9b-81d6-91ee0c039409","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Advantages of Options","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"da9184e4-ec13-4d25-a6fb-d9c2d9b226d5"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"16a7d63d-4d71-4191-b6ee-626599c19278","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Why might a firm choose to hedge with options rather than forward contracts? Many managers want the firm to benefit if the exchange rate moves in its favor, rather than being stuck paying an above-market rate. Firms also prefer options to forward contracts if the transaction they are hedging might not take place. In this case, a forward contract could commit them to making an exchange at an unfavorable rate for currency they do not need, whereas an option allows them to walk away from the exchange. In any case, it is worth noting that an option holder can always sell the position at a gain rather than demanding delivery of the currency, so if the transaction does not take place and the option is in-the-money, the company need not actually demand delivery of the foreign currency.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"a6e24844-6d25-409b-9ec9-70980d6ca8ce"}]}]}]},{"cssClass":"aside-group Sidebar_1Aside","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"0ee35201-2cb9-484d-b1bf-b86fd1bf1c47","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Concept Check","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"1d0bba09-995a-421d-a0d6-4072970e1e14"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":3},"ref":"1f1fffe5-e648-4451-a7bf-9ae1b0d8d631","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"c6b7fff0-e986-48c3-a698-23d992452a5a","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"e2d68887-e7d3-4507-97c8-6a5ea75de0aa","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"How can firms hedge exchange rate risk?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"8b8ae095-a6c5-40b2-bba7-cf50b70d58aa","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"6a54af34-2eb7-4de9-b674-fbf45ad9adad","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Why might a firm prefer to hedge exchange rate risk with options rather than forward contracts?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"e7bafc14-6805-428a-8d2a-c6534c9cb58c"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockE